<p>Every strong company starts with an advanced Human Resources team, they are the backbone of the company responsible for hiring, firing, and attracting new talent.</p>
<p>And while titles like Head of People and Chief People Officer are trending, the role of Human Resources Business Partner is also becoming more vital. So, how does HRBP play a significant role in&#xA0;<strong>enhancing employee experience and business outcomes</strong>? And what do they do?</p>
<p>We&#x2019;re here to answer those critical questions and demonstrate to you how this position can grow your business.</p>
<p>This article will teach you everything you need to know about HRBP. We'll cover the meaning, core responsibilities, the main difference between HRBP and HR manager, and how you can shift from HR administrator to HRBP.</p>
